A portion of Grotte de Vitane is exposed to full sunlight, and there is a short (
1 m
) undercut shelf along the otherwise sheer walls that was not directly exposed; however, the dark, subterranean portion of this particular system extended much further than one could snorkel on a breath of air, and remains unknown. Although we only encountered a few individuals in the sinkhole, all were darkly pigmented and blind. Given that portions of the sinkhole receive direct sunlight, possession of uniformly dark brown body coloration may function to camouflage individuals from predators or offer protection from UV radiation.
